{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Brody Jenner | image = Brody Jenner (cropped).jpg | caption = Jenner in 2008 | image_size = 200px | birth_name = Sam Brody Jenner | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1983|8|21}} | birth_place = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S. | residence = [[Malibu, California]], U.S. | occupation = Television personality, model, socialite | years_active = 2005–present | television = {{plainlist| * ''[[The Princes of Malibu]]'' * ''[[The Hills (TV series)|The Hills]]'' * ''[[Bromance (TV series)|Bromance]]'' * ''[[Keeping Up with the Kardashians]]'' * ''[[Sex with Brody]]''}} | parents = {{plainlist| * [[Bruce Jenner]] * [[Linda Thompson (actress)|Linda Thompson]] }} | spouse(s) = {{marriage|Kaitlynn Carter|June 2, 2018}} | relatives = {{plainlist| * [[Brandon Jenner]] <small>(brother)</small> * [[Burt Jenner]] <small>(half-brother)</small> * [[Casey Jenner]] <small>(half-sister)</small> * [[Kendall Jenner]] <small>(half-sister)</small> * [[Kylie Jenner]] <small>(half-sister)</small> }} }}
'''Sam Brody Jenner'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/mar/05/entertainment/la-et-mg-brody-jenner-joins-kardashians-20130305|title=Brody Jenner joins 'Keeping Up With the Kardashians'|author=Nardine Saad|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=[[Tribune Company]]|date=March 5, 2013|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref> (born August 21, 1983)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/brody_jenner/biography/|title=Brody Jenner Biography|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=July 23, 2013}}</ref> is an American television personality, socialite, and model. The son of [[Bruce Jenner]] and actress [[Linda Thompson (actress)|Linda Thompson]], he was born and raised in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. In 2005, Jenner appeared in the [[reality television]] series, ''[[The Princes of Malibu]]'', which additionally featured his eldest brother, [[Brandon Jenner]], and his friend, [[Spencer Pratt]].
In 2007, he began dating [[Lauren Conrad]], a primary cast member of ''[[The Hills (TV series)|The Hills]]'', and subsequently came to prominence after being cast in the series during the second season. Their brief relationship ultimately ended his friendship with Pratt. The following year, Jenner was commissioned in his own [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series, ''[[Bromance (TV series)|Bromance]]'', in which he was intended to find another companion in Pratt's absence. However, it was canceled after its inaugural season after receiving underwhelming ratings.
In 2009, Conrad left ''The Hills'' to pursue other career opportunities and was replaced by Jenner's ex-girlfriend, [[Kristin Cavallari]]. Their rekindled relationship became the central focus of the series until its conclusion the following year. In 2013, Jenner returned to reality television, appearing on ''[[Keeping Up with the Kardashians]]'' during its eighth season, which featured Bruce and his stepmother [[Kris Jenner]]; his stepsiblings, [[Kourtney Kardashian|Kourtney]], [[Kim Kardashian|Kim]], [[Khloé Kardashian|Khloé]], and [[Rob Kardashian|Rob]]; and his half-sisters, [[Kendall Jenner|Kendall]] and [[Kylie Jenner]].
==Life and career== Jenner was born in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], on August 21, 1983, to reality television personality and retired [[1976 Summer Olympics|Olympics]] champion [[Bruce Jenner]] (formerly Bruce Jenner) and actress [[Linda Thompson (actress)|Linda Thompson]]. He is the half-brother to Burton "Burt" and Cassandra "Casey" Jenner through Caitlyn's marriage to Chrystie Crownover, which lasted from 1972 until 1981. Jenner is the younger brother of Brandon Jenner, also a reality-television personality.
After Jenner's parents divorced in 1985, Bruce Jenner married [[Kris Jenner|Kris Kardashian]], the ex-wife of attorney [[Robert Kardashian]], in 1991. Consequently, Jenner became a stepbrother of [[Kourtney Kardashian|Kourtney]], [[Kim Kardashian|Kim]], [[Khloé Kardashian|Khloé]], and [[Rob Kardashian]]. Kris gave birth to his half-sisters [[Kendall Jenner|Kendall]] and [[Kylie Jenner]] in 1995 and 1997.
Also in 1991, Thompson remarried to composer and record producer [[David Foster]]. In 2005, Thompson, Foster, the Jenner brothers, and their friend [[Spencer Pratt]] starred in the [[reality television]] series ''[[The Princes of Malibu]]''. However, the series was cancelled soon after its premiere when Thompson filed for divorce from Foster.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0464767/plotsummary|title=The Princes of Malibu Plot Summary|accessdate=2012-03-03}}</ref>
In 2006, [[MTV]] developed the reality television series ''[[The Hills (TV series)|The Hills]]'' as the [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] of ''[[Laguna Beach: The Real Orange County]]''. It originally chronicled the lives of [[Lauren Conrad]], who appeared on its predecessor, her housemate [[Heidi Montag]], and friends [[Audrina Patridge]] and [[Whitney Port]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/31/arts/television/31heff.html?_r=1&oref=slogin|title='The Hills,' a Follow-Up to 'Laguna Beach,' Makes Its Premiere on MTV|author= Virginia Heffernan|work=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=May 31, 2006|accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref> In 2007, Jenner began dating Conrad, which led to the deterioration with his friendship with Pratt. After Conrad established companionships with Jenner and [[Frankie Delgado]], Pratt severed ties with both men.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/shows/the_hills/season_3/episode.jhtml?episodeID=120176|title=The Hills (Season 3) Ep. 305: Rolling With The Enemy|work=MTV|publisher=Viacom|date=September 3, 2007|accessdate=May 16, 2013}}</ref>
In 2009, Jenner hosted and Executive produced his own reality show ''[[Bromance (TV series)|Bromance]]'', in which young men competed to become part of his entourage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/shows/bromance/cast.jhtml|title=Bromance Cast Bios|accessdate=2012-03-03}}</ref> Jenner has modeled for [[Guess (clothing)|Guess]] clothing, [[Agent Provocateur (lingerie)|Agent Provocateur]] underwear,<ref>White, Nicholas. [http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,1548619,00.html Brody Jenner & Lauren Conrad: An Item] People</ref> [[Ocean Pacific|OP]],<ref>[http://www.usmagazine.com/news/sneak-peak-sophia-bush-hits-the-beach-with-brody-jenner-200984 SNEAK PEEK: Sophia Bush Hits the Beach With Brody Jenner] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411025319/http://www.usmagazine.com/news/sneak-peak-sophia-bush-hits-the-beach-with-brody-jenner-200984 |date=April 11, 2009 }} Us magazine. 4.8.2009</ref> and the magazine ''[[Cosmogirl]]''.<ref>[http://www.cosmogirl.com/guys/eyecandy/eye-candy-brody-jenner Brody Jenner] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090409022803/http://www.cosmogirl.com/guys/eyecandy/eye-candy-brody-jenner |date=April 9, 2009 }} CosmoGirl</ref>
