{{BLP sources|date=March 2011}}
'''Dixon Seeto''' ({{zh|t=司徒新耀|p=Sītú Xīnyào}}) is a [[Fiji]]an businessman and political leader of Chinese descent. He has been President of the [[Fiji Islands Hotel and Tourism Association]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?id=160615 | title=Tourism's $25m wish|author=Shalveen Chand | publisher= The Fiji Times ONLINE | date=26 November 2010 | accessdate=9 December 2010}}</ref> and of the [[Chinese Association of Fiji]].  In June 2006 he was appointed to the Fijian [[Senate of Fiji|Senate]] as one of 9 nominees of the Prime Minister, [[Laisenia Qarase]].

On completing his secondary education in 1969, Seeto worked initially for [[Air Pacific]] and later for [[Tapa International]] together with David Wilson and the [[Warwick Hotel]].  From 1971 to 1974, he was employed by [[British Airways]] while studying aviation in London, on a scholarship.  Upon graduating, he rejoined Air Pacific, where he remained until 1987.  Since then, he has been in the private sector.

On 10 December 2005, Seeto won the [[2005 Excellence Award (Fiji)|2005 Excellence Award]] for his contribution to the tourism industry, the [[Fiji Times]] reported the following day.

