'''Goh Cheng Liang''' ({{zh|s=吴清亮|zh|t=吳清亮|p=Wú Qīng Liàng}}; born 1927/28) is a Singaporean [[billionaire]] businessman who founded Wuthelam Holdings, which manufactures paint and coatings.<ref name="Bloomberg 2015">{{cite web|last=Wong|first=Sterling|date=January 19, 2015|title=Raffles Hotel Job Helps Make Goh Cheng Liang Singapore’s Richest|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/billionaires/headline/raffles-hotel-job-helps-make-billionaire-goh-cheng-liang-singapore-s-richest-1|website=Bloomberg Billionaires|publisher=Bloomberg LLC|accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref>
==Biography== Goh Cheng Liang was born in Singapore.<ref name=Forbes/> He set up his first paint shop there in 1955, and became the main distributor there for [[Nippon Paint]] in 1962.<ref name=NP>{{cite web|title=Our History|url=http://www.nipponpaint.com.sg/about-us/our-history|website=Nippon Paint SG|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref> Wuthelam Holdings, which now has interests in the paint business and property development, was founded in 1974 as a real estate concern.<ref name="Bloomberg 2015" />
==Personal life== He lives in Singapore.<ref name=Forbes/> His Goh Foundation has made large donations to several charitable causes.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Hui Chieh|title=$12m gift for leukaemia research|url=https://www.nuh.com.sg/wbn/slot/u1753/Patients%20and%20Visitors/Media%20Articles/Mar%2009/5th%20ST%20$12m.pdf|website=National University Hospital Singapore|publisher=The Straits Times Singapore|accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Goh Foundation Endowed Scholarship|url=http://www.smu.edu.sg/about/financial/scholarships/Goh_Foundation|website=Singapore Management University|publisher=Singapore Management University|accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref>
He has a son, [[Goh Hup Jin]], who has been the chairman of Nippon Paint since March 2018 and runs their privately-held joint venture, [[Nipsea]].<ref name=Forbes/>
