'''Phi Lambda Sigma''' ('''ΦΛΣ''') is an American college honor society for pharmacy students. It was founded at [[Auburn University]] in March 1965,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pharmacist.com/article/fifty-years-leadership|title=Fifty years of leadership|website=www.pharmacist.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> and in 2018 had approximately 30,000 members.<ref name=ACHSNATL>{{cite web|url=http://achsnatl.org/society.asp?society=pls&honor_society=Phi_Lambda_Sigma|title=Phi Lambda Sigma Honor Society- Pharmacy - An ACHS Member Society|website=achsnatl.org|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> The mission of Phi Lambda Sigma, also known as the national Pharmacy Leadership Society, is to support pharmacy leadership commitment by recognizing leaders and fostering leadership development.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://philambdasigma.org/PLS/Mission/tabid/103/Default.aspx|title=Mission|website=philambdasigma.org|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> The society was admitted to the [[Association of College Honor Societies]] (ACHS) in 2018.<ref name=ACHSNATL/>

