'''''RCR Wireless News''''' is a weekly [[wireless]] [[telecommunications]] industry [[trade publication]].<ref name="prne"/>

==History and profile==
''RCR Wireless'' was started in 1982.<ref name="prne">{{cite news|title=RCR Wireless News Announces Online TV News and Instructional Programs|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2014/11/prweb12295001.htm|accessdate=25 September 2016|work=PR Newswire|date=3 November 2014|location=Austin, Texas}}</ref> On March 3, 2009, the magazine was shut down by [[Crain Communications]]. The publication was sold to Arden Media Company, and relaunched in September 2009 with the same editorial team.<ref name="relaunch">[http://www.rcrwireless.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20090901/FRONTPAGE/908319991/Letter-from-the-Publishers Letter from the Publishers]{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

''RCR Wireless News''’ [[editorial]] team is led by Tracy Ford.<ref>[http://www.rcrwireless.com/section&template=editorialTeam Editorial team] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080924141611/http://www.rcrwireless.com/section%26template%3DeditorialTeam |date=2008-09-24 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.rcrwireless.com/section/Columnists?tag=Tracy%20Ford&tagid=3588 Tracy Ford]</ref> The headquarters was in [[Golden, Colorado]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Directory of Market Publications|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=umIkmrQD8TAC&pg=PA14|accessdate=25 September 2016|publisher=BoogarLists|page=14|id=GGKEY:F1Q8R91EH9W}}</ref>

